Package gg.valgo.gradian

Class Gradian

  • java.lang.Object
    • gg.valgo.gradian.Gradian
  • public class Gradian
extends Object
    The main Gradian class, with methods to create and combine parsers, as well as static parsers.

    • Field Detail

      • digit

        public static final RegexParser digit
        A parser which matches a digit. This parser results in a string. This parser fails if the next character in the input is not a digit. This parser returns a string.

      • digits

        public static final RegexParser digits
        A parser which matches 1 or more digits. This parser results in a string. This parser fails if the next character in the input is not a digit. Otherwise, it will match digits until the next character is not a digit. This parser returns a string.

      • letter

        public static final RegexParser letter
        A parser which matches a letter. This parser results in a string. This parser fails if the next character in the input is not a letter. This parser returns a string.

      • letters

        public static final RegexParser letters
        A parser which parses 1 or more letters. This parser results in a string. This parser fails if the next character in the input is not a letter. Otherwise, it will match letters until the next character is not a letter. This parser returns a string.

      • whitespace

        public static final RegexParser whitespace
        A parser which matches any whitespace characters, up until the next non-whitespace character. This parser fails if the next character in the input is not a whitespace character. If you wish for whitespace to be optional, use `Gradian.optionalWhitespace` instead. The parser will match whitespace characters until the next character is not a whitespace character. This parser returns a string.

      • optionalWhitespace

        public static final Parser<String> optionalWhitespace
        A parser which optionally matches any whitespace character. If there is no whitespace present, it returns an empty string. Otherwise, it will return a string with the whitespace. This parser will match all whitespace characters, up until a non-whitespace character. This parser returns a string.

      • anyCharacter

        public static final AnyCharacterParser anyCharacter
        A parser which matches any character. It results in a character, or a string if `.asString()` is called. This parser will only fail if the end of input has been reached. This parser returns a character, or a string if `.asString()` is called.

      • endOfInput

        public static final EndOfInputParser endOfInput
        This parser matches the end of the input. It results in a null value. This parser will fail if the end of input has not been reached. This parser returns a null value.

      • regex

        public static RegexParser regex​(String pattern)
        A parser which matches a regular expression in a string. If matching was successful, the match is returned. Otherwise, the parser fails. This parser only accepts string input.
        Parameters:

      • regex

        public static RegexParser regex​(String pattern,
                                int flags,
                                int group)
        A parser which matches a regular expression in a string. If matching was successful, the match (or a group within the match) is returned. Otherwise, the parser fails. This parser only accepts string input.
        Parameters:
        pattern - The pattern to match. All patterns should start with a "^" character, so that only the current input is matched.
        flags - The regex flags, use 0 for no flags.
        group - The group in the regex to use as the result. Use 0 to result in the entire match.
        Returns:
        The regex parser.

        Parameters:
        parsers - The parsers to choose from.
        Returns:
        The choice parser.
